					<contentItem id="126">
						<title>
							
						</title>
						<text>
							The Sloth is the world's slowest mammal! They are too slow to outrun predators, but they do have extra long necks that can turn 270 degrees to see danger around them. If they are above the water, they will sometimes drop down to evade a predator and swim to safety. They are strong swimmers!
						</text>
